{
  "texts": [
    "Users can click on the highlighted text to accept or reject the changes.",
    "Inspired by LangChain, Wordflow allows users to add optional output parsing rules to a prompt by writing regular expression (regex) text (Fig. 3).",
    "For example, a user can prompt LLMs to structure the output in XML format (recommended by prompt engineering guidelines [5]), such as \"Improve the flow of the following text.",
    "Put the rewritten text in an XML tag <output></output>\".",
    "The user can then add a regex pattern.*<output>(.*)</output>."
  ]
}